cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM

This paper deals with visualizing and understanding convolutional networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the performance contribution from different model layers and finding model architectures that outperform previous benchmarks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions generalizing the ImageNet model to other datasets, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
